AB Negative publicity can diminish positive consumer perceptions of a
   brand. We explore the impact of processing style on mitigating the
   effects of negative publicity. We hypothesize that holistic thinkers are
   less susceptible to negative publicity information than are analytic
   thinkers. Holistic thinkers are more likely to consider external
   context-based explanations for the negative publicity, resulting in
   little or no revision of belief's about the parent brand. Analytic
