   live. Due to the complexity of food decision making, consumers are
   susceptible to a wide range of social, cognitive, affective, and
   environmental forces determined to interrupt their intentions to
   restrict their dietary intake. In this article, we integrate literature
   from diverse theoretical perspectives into a conceptual framework
   designed to offer a better understanding of the antecedents,
