   domain of interest to the consumer psychologist. ANNs are mathematical
   models that are commonly used in business applications to model
   relationships between variables. A key strength of ANNs is their
   flexibility, i.e. their ability to easily accommodate linear and
   non-linear relationships without any a priori functional form
