AB The primary goal of this research is to conceptualize and develop a
   scale of green consumption values, which we define as the tendency to
   express the value of environmental protection through one's purchases
   and consumption behaviors. Across six studies, we demonstrate that the
   six-item measure we develop (i.e., the GREEN scale) can be used to
   capture green consumption values in a reliable, valid, and parsimonious
