   outlines two general approaches that can lead to further our
   understanding of the variety of ways emotions affect decision-making and
   information processing. Specifically, future research can examine the
   nature of emotional appraisals or investigate the nature of decision
   contexts and underlying psychological processes influenced by emotions.
